00:58:43,587 --> 00:58:47,127
The one with "Friends Forever"
is really fantastic.

558
00:58:47,724 --> 00:58:52,034
And this is an actor.
He does a lot of preparation

559
00:58:52,763 --> 00:59:03,723
and chooses the suitable role,
and he keeps on adding things.

560
00:59:05,509 --> 00:59:07,729
This is a good actor
who cooperates with others.

561
00:59:42,712 --> 00:59:44,852
SIU FAI MAK: We were
looking for a bodyguard character

562
00:59:45,215 --> 00:59:46,645
beside Ngai Wing-Hau.

563
00:59:46,950 --> 00:59:51,609
This bodyguard
has been working for years,

564
00:59:52,489 --> 00:59:56,469
and he has to be strongly built,

565
00:59:58,962 --> 01:00:09,812
the kind of guy who can take you
by the throat with or without guns.

566
01:00:11,541 --> 01:00:19,631
When we were designing this role,
we tried to give him a few lines,

567
01:00:20,851 --> 01:00:27,181
but they turned out to be
almost always the same--

568
01:00:28,158 --> 01:00:33,837
"Luo Ji has a covetous eye."

569
01:00:34,764 --> 01:00:38,544
After having written this same line
maybe five times,

570
01:00:39,169 --> 01:00:42,269
you'd finally just go,
"Just give him a line!"

571
01:00:42,806 --> 01:00:45,556
Like when Ngai Wing-Hau
asks him, "How about that?"

572
01:00:46,042 --> 01:00:47,502
He says, "Okay!"
Things like that.

573
01:00:47,811 --> 01:00:53,671
Later on, when we approached
Yiu-Yeung Cheung, we said,

574
01:00:54,551 --> 01:00:58,681
"We have this role. Do you want it?"

575
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:02,269
Of course the role has its appeal.

576
01:01:02,792 --> 01:01:13,752
He is an undercover cop,
undercover for many years.

577
01:01:15,539 --> 01:01:20,289
When we cast
it with Yiu-Yeung Cheung,

578
01:01:21,044 --> 01:01:23,734
after the first day's shoot,
Yiu-Yeung Cheung stood there quietly,

579
01:01:24,214 --> 01:01:28,194
which was a little scary
and made me kind of worried.

580
01:01:28,885 --> 01:01:30,345
Wai Keung Lau knows him well,
so he didn't care a bit.

581
01:01:30,654 --> 01:01:34,284
He just kept saying, "You stay here.
Don't move, and no talking.”

582
01:01:34,925 --> 01:01:43,455
And he kept saying this all day long.

583
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:46,981
When we saw him standing there
motionlessly looking at us,

584
01:01:47,571 --> 01:01:48,941
we wondered if he was getting mad.

585
01:01:49,206 --> 01:01:50,636
Do we need to write more lines for him?

586
01:01:50,941 --> 01:01:53,491
If he cannot stand it and decides
to beat us, there would be problems.

587
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:56,520
We declined to add any lines for him,

588
01:01:56,947 --> 01:01:58,677
but we found
this role really needs no talk.

589
01:01:59,015 --> 01:02:00,654
When Yiu-Yeung Cheung is playing it,

590
01:02:00,984 --> 01:02:03,614
there is no need for him to talk
throughout the movie.

591
01:02:04,087 --> 01:02:08,367
This is when you begin thinking about
why this person is so strange.

592
01:02:09,092 --> 01:02:13,572
What the hell does he do?

593
01:02:14,297 --> 01:02:21,037
When we reach the middle part
of the movie, we all know who he is.

594
01:02:22,072 --> 01:02:24,322
At some point,
the expression in his eyes

595
01:02:24,708 --> 01:02:28,248
tells us there is something
he wants to tell Chan Wing Yan,

596
01:02:28,845 --> 01:02:30,865
whose undercover identity he knows.

597
01:02:31,214 --> 01:02:34,174
He wants to caution his young friend
about the danger.

598
01:02:34,684 --> 01:02:38,964
On the other hand, this character
wants Chan Wing Yan to know

599
01:02:39,623 --> 01:02:42,433
this is the fate of those
who go deep undercover.

600
01:02:42,959 --> 01:02:44,979
WAI KEUNG LAU:
If were to tell some professional actors

601
01:02:45,528 --> 01:02:51,647
l had a character for them,
but without so much as a single line,

602
01:02:52,602 --> 01:02:55,182
I think most of them would take this
as a formidable challenge.

603
01:02:55,639 --> 01:02:58,599
Yiu-Yeung Cheung thought so too.

604
01:02:59,109 --> 01:03:02,449
At first he actually had one line,

605
01:03:03,013 --> 01:03:06,232
and he asked us if we could add another.

606
01:03:06,783 --> 01:03:08,593
I said yes, with much thought.

607
01:03:08,918 --> 01:03:13,868
Actually, I didn't want there to be
any lines for him.

608
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:18,024
But this seemed unfair to him.
With just one line, we had him in.

609
01:03:18,595 --> 01:03:24,774
Later on, he kept asking for lines,
and I gave him one that was absurd.

610
01:03:25,735 --> 01:03:29,195
That is, right before his death, he says,

611
01:03:29,739 --> 01:03:32,669
"Mr. Ngai, you are not
like this, are you?"

612
01:03:33,176 --> 01:03:36,456
He said, "I can't do this."

613
01:03:37,013 --> 01:03:40,113
I said, "I know, so why don't you just
try not speaking when you play it.”

614
01:03:40,650 --> 01:03:42,380
And in the end,
he even didn't say this line.

615
01:03:55,832 --> 01:03:57,062
CARINA LAU: Actually, for Mary,

616
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:01,310
she doesn't need to look at
Lau Kin Ming when talking with him.

617
01:04:01,938 --> 01:04:06,888
They are boss and underling,
senior and junior.

618
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:12,507
When talking to him,
she will treat him like a child

619
01:04:13,283 --> 01:04:17,883
and not care much
what his inner feelings may be.

620
01:04:18,621 --> 01:04:22,191
Because she brings him up,
she never thinks

621
01:04:22,792 --> 01:04:27,011
about the possibility of
a love affair occurring between them.

622
01:04:27,697 --> 01:04:35,637
But when Lau Kin Ming grows up,
he begins to take notice of her,

623
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:38,830
which goes totally unnoticed by Mary.

624
01:04:39,209 --> 01:04:42,719
Whenever Mary looks at
Lau Kin Ming, he shies away.

