908
01:37:04,619 --> 01:37:10,799
Whatever you do,
you should endeavor to have the music

909
01:37:12,627 --> 01:37:23,117
complement and amplify
every scene in the film.

910
01:37:24,672 --> 01:37:28,482
We had known each other so well
after years of cooperation.

911
01:37:33,214 --> 01:37:43,674
Say I wanted a piano
or a symphony,

912
01:37:45,226 --> 01:37:49,326
I would talk with him
before we ever shot that scene.

913
01:37:49,964 --> 01:37:51,714
That way he would have a better grasp.

914
01:38:51,225 --> 01:38:53,275
SIU FAI MAK:
Here we see the sparkle

915
01:38:53,628 --> 01:38:55,527
between Eric Tsang and Francis Ng.

916
01:38:55,897 --> 01:39:03,637
When we were doing it the first time,
everybody's timing was just right.

917
01:39:04,806 --> 01:39:07,875
Because Wai Keung Lau is a director
who doesn't like rehearsals.

918
01:39:08,543 --> 01:39:15,133
He wanted the rehearsal over with
before the lighting was done.

919
01:39:16,150 --> 01:39:24,150
Sometimes once the set was lit,
he wanted no rehearsal. "Let's shoot!"

920
01:39:26,294 --> 01:39:30,654
Eric and Francis
were servant and master.

921
01:39:31,499 --> 01:39:38,358
You could see that from their costumes.

922
01:39:39,574 --> 01:39:46,193
You take a look at them, and you know
that Eric is Francis’ servant.

923
01:39:47,215 --> 01:39:53,665
When they walk together,
it just feels right.

924
01:39:54,655 --> 01:39:57,405
Their physical appearance,
their costumes--all very natural.

925
01:39:57,892 --> 01:40:02,312
It's all so natural,
and they even had chemistry.

926
01:40:03,030 --> 01:40:11,620
Especially in that last scene,
where Francis invited Eric for a drink.

927
01:40:12,874 --> 01:40:18,264
We didn't have that in the script,
but they acted it out.

928
01:40:19,080 --> 01:40:20,780
That's amazing.

929
01:40:21,082 --> 01:40:22,982
For example, Francis poured wine
for Eric, but Eric pushed the glass away.

930
01:40:23,518 --> 01:40:25,688
Then Francis handed the phone to Eric.

931
01:40:26,087 --> 01:40:32,207
Those things happen at the table, but
the tension ripples to Hawaii and Thailand.

932
01:40:33,127 --> 01:40:39,747
I think what they brought to their roles
was greater than what was in the script.

933
01:40:44,872 --> 01:40:47,332
ERIC TSANG: I love that scene too.

934
01:40:47,775 --> 01:40:49,945
The rhythm of acting is important.

935
01:40:50,511 --> 01:40:53,121
I do not necessarily respond
to a line at once.

936
01:40:53,548 --> 01:40:54,947
Take that scene.

937
01:40:55,216 --> 01:40:59,966
He raised the glass, but I silently
watched him, then pushed the glass away.

938
01:41:00,721 --> 01:41:05,550
Actually, by pushing away the glass,
I was letting him know I didn't agree.

939
01:41:06,294 --> 01:41:16,144
Then he handed me the phone,
suggesting I'm under his thumb.

940
01:41:17,638 --> 01:41:20,388
But what he didn't know
was that I had him well in hand.

941
01:41:20,875 --> 01:41:24,355
When we exchanged the phone,
we had made everything clear.

942
01:41:24,946 --> 01:41:34,706
Just like I said,
I enjoyed the interaction between us.

943
01:41:36,157 --> 01:41:46,737
Actually from infernal Affairs !
to internal Affairs Il,

944
01:41:48,302 --> 01:41:57,621
l had been enjoying the process
of collaborating with fine actors.

945
01:41:59,013 --> 01:42:05,813
l had been going around saying
l regained my acting bug last year.

946
01:42:06,854 --> 01:42:08,784
l had fun, so now I'm producing.

947
01:42:09,123 --> 01:42:12,692
Everybody is waiting for a good story.

948
01:42:13,294 --> 01:42:16,314
A good cast of actors.
Everybody worked well together.

949
01:42:16,797 --> 01:42:18,547
What we used to do
were mostly comedies.

950
01:42:18,866 --> 01:42:24,086
The comedians got together
to play something funny.

951
01:42:24,905 --> 01:42:28,184
This time it's a serious movie,

952
01:42:28,743 --> 01:42:31,373
and we were serious about details,
about eye contact, about mannerisms.

953
01:42:31,846 --> 01:42:36,236
You gave me this role,
so [ had to bring my best into play.

954
01:42:36,951 --> 01:42:41,841
Francis wanted to talk about the scene
where he died at the hawker stand.

955
01:42:42,590 --> 01:42:45,250
Actually, we wanted to do
a trial before that.

956
01:42:45,726 --> 01:42:51,816
See what each of us
has brought to the movie.

957
01:42:52,733 --> 01:42:57,593
Put everybody's performance together,
and you have a good movie.

958
01:42:58,539 --> 01:43:04,369
Everybody had different ideas.
We saw what's best.

959
01:43:05,279 --> 01:43:09,939
Francis felt that way too.
Everyone shared their ideas.

960
01:43:10,685 --> 01:43:14,605
Everyone got new ideas for acting.

961
01:43:15,256 --> 01:43:21,736
It may be different from
what you came up with.

962
01:43:22,697 --> 01:43:28,677
You just act it out.
And it is different from a stereotype.

963
01:43:36,544 --> 01:43:39,174
FRANCIS WOO:
l have tremendous respect for Eric.

964
01:43:39,647 --> 01:43:41,077
As a matter of fact...

965
01:43:44,752 --> 01:43:49,062
One day we had a few drinks,
and he said something

966
01:43:49,757 --> 01:43:54,826
that gave me the confidence
and determination to portray this role

967
01:43:55,629 --> 01:43:58,559
without "acting" that much.

968
01:43:59,033 --> 01:44:01,753
He told me, "You look
quite aggressive yourself.

969
01:44:02,236 --> 01:44:07,016
Don't act. Get another day job."

970
01:44:07,775 --> 01:44:13,424
So I didn't act.
I dealt with him in my own way.

971
01:44:14,482 --> 01:44:16,062
It's interesting, I think.

972
01:44:16,550 --> 01:44:25,580
It's a rare thing to have such intimate
acting with a male actor.

973
01:44:29,063 --> 01:44:37,793
We had a tacit understanding,
and it's terrific.

974
01:44:39,140 --> 01:44:44,060
It's like we fell in love
with each other,

975
01:44:44,879 --> 01:44:51,029
since we had
such good communication.

976
01:44:51,986 --> 01:44:53,766
ERIC TSANG:
Il told him not to act,

977
01:44:54,121 --> 01:44:58,101
because his role was already
in the right place.

978
01:44:58,759 --> 01:45:03,149
He didn't have to deepen the role.

979
01:45:03,864 --> 01:45:11,254
This character was already very
dramatic, so he just played it casually.

980
01:45:12,540 --> 01:45:18,870
If you portrayed a dramatic
character in a dramatic way,

981
01:45:19,847 --> 01:45:22,567
it'd become a stage play.

982
01:45:23,050 --> 01:45:25,270
You can't play too hard.

983
01:45:25,686 --> 01:45:31,456
What pleases me most
is that we talk everything over.

984
01:45:32,493 --> 01:45:36,393
l offer some advice,
which you could just ignore.

985
01:45:37,031 --> 01:45:39,871
But for me, I speak it out, ! am happy.

986
01:45:40,501 --> 01:45:42,081
You don't have to accept that.

987
01:45:42,536 --> 01:45:48,926
We exchanged our opinions,
but we didn't impose ourselves.

988
01:45:49,944 --> 01:45:51,674
Everybody was willing to offer advice.

989
01:45:52,012 --> 01:45:55,552
It's not like we hid what we had

990
01:45:56,150 --> 01:46:01,480
and pulled it out to show
only during the performance itself.

991
01:46:02,289 --> 01:46:08,379
People did that in times past,

992
01:46:09,296 --> 01:46:13,366
but in this movie, we were
all open and willing to share.

993
01:46:39,260 --> 01:46:42,360
Even in the last scene,
between Anthony and me,

994
01:46:42,863 --> 01:46:56,113
he said, "You have screwed up
everything I have tried to do."

995
01:46:58,045 --> 01:47:01,235
He's supposed
to act out his inner world.

996
01:47:01,749 --> 01:47:06,228
I think he should take
the credit for that scene.

997
01:47:06,921 --> 01:47:12,931
l wanted him to succeed
in ways I never could.

998
01:47:13,827 --> 01:47:20,097
Acting is like playing football.
You have to pass the ball.

999
01:47:21,035 --> 01:47:24,075
If l can't score,
at least I can pass the ball

1000
01:47:24,571 --> 01:47:26,791
to a teammate who has a chance.

1001
01:47:27,207 --> 01:47:29,787
I'd rather do this.
After all, it's a game.

1002
01:47:30,244 --> 01:47:33,554
It's a matter of teamwork,
not individualism.

1003
01:47:34,081 --> 01:47:36,801
I think that infernal Affairs
is that kind of a movie--

1004
01:47:37,251 --> 01:47:42,491
a great piece of teamwork,
not a showcase for loners.

1005
01:47:43,490 --> 01:47:45,950
The audiences just love the movie.

1006
01:49:11,912 --> 01:49:13,552
SIU FAI MAK: Why end the story

1007
01:49:13,881 --> 01:49:16,191
on the night of Hong Kong's
return in 1997?

1008
01:49:16,583 --> 01:49:18,312
It's an important historical moment,

1009
01:49:18,652 --> 01:49:22,222
for every person in Hong Kong.

1010
01:49:22,790 --> 01:49:25,600
Since that night,
everything has changed.

1011
01:49:26,093 --> 01:49:32,603
That moment fits this story.

1012
01:49:33,600 --> 01:49:41,070
A background befitting the theme
of the movie was selected.

1013
01:49:42,209 --> 01:49:43,438
We were attracted to this.

1014
01:49:43,677 --> 01:49:49,826
After the script was finished,
I told everyone about the actors.

1015
01:49:50,751 --> 01:49:57,901
I said that Infernal Affairs Il
was a stand-alone script.

1016
01:49:58,959 --> 01:50:02,769
It would be a wonderful script
even without Internal Affairs I.

1017
01:50:03,530 --> 01:50:07,690
But it might never have been shot.

1018
01:50:08,502 --> 01:50:12,132
There are many elements

1019
01:50:12,739 --> 01:50:23,409
that you can't just weave
into a sequel that easily.

1020
01:50:24,952 --> 01:50:27,822
lam not talking about
the commercial elements.

1021
01:50:28,489 --> 01:50:29,829
I don't think so.

1022
01:50:30,090 --> 01:50:37,920
It's a really long story, and a lot
of people are concerned about this.

1023
01:50:39,133 --> 01:50:42,673
Then you can put these things
in the story.

1024
01:50:44,838 --> 01:50:46,388
That's the way it is.

1025
01:50:48,475 --> 01:50:49,785
Without infernal Affairs 1,

1026
01:50:50,077 --> 01:50:53,267
Infernal Affairs tl
would ignore the times for sure.

1027
01:50:53,814 --> 01:51:01,494
It would only deal with changed people,
a simple story of people.

1028
01:51:02,656 --> 01:51:09,956
Being able to do this
has made me grateful.

